5:
All right, Nimbus. Did you finish the 
practice sheet I assigned you last 
time?
12:
I see. You did not complete your 
homework.
24:
Oh great, here comes trouble...
As you can see, we're studying.
31:
If you're just here to be annoying, 
shoo.
34:
Currently, we are practicing reading 
and writing.
37: You can teach people to read?
40: Yes, I am a strong reader myself.
50:
What's that? Your book looks old as 
hell, man.
53:
The priest who made my demon-
hunting gear had this. It's some kind 
of guide to demons.
54:
Where they come from, what turns 
human into them, that kinda stuff.
56:
Most importantly, it should have 
information on how to kill them. 
Can you read it?
61: From the looks of this, yes.
68: Learn to read it yourself, Asukirimaru.
72:
Huh? She said she can read it for me, 
so why bother?
75:
Look, I'm not Light, so if you wanna go 
duke it out with demons, I won't stop 
you.
77:
But combat training's on YOU, not 
Stella. She teaches ABCs, not fighting.
82:
I never said she has to practice the 
techniques with me, I just need 
someone to read them for me!
85:
Then looks like you better sit down 
and start learnin' your letters.
88:
Hmph, you sound like that smiley 
samurai bastard...
94:
Nothing. Just sounded like something 
a guy back home would say.
100:
We were just about to start our lesson. 
Please take a seat, and we'll begin.
110:
Haha, good luck! She's a strict teacher,
 so you'd better watch out.
115:
That goes for you as well, Nimbus. 
Please start by writing all of the letters 
in alphabetical order.
120:
Huh? W-wait, ALL of them? Leave me 
outta this, I just wanna read Rolan's 
old stuff.
123:
I expect you to provide a good role-
model for the new classmate you 
invited.
143:
If it'll bring me closer to busting that 
bastard, I'll be the best damn reader 
ever!
146:
You're here to learn your ABCs, 
dumbass. Quit actin' cool.
151: You can't read either! OLD dumbass!
156:
Oh yeah? Try sayin' that again, 
you tiny brat!
162:
This is a library. I expect indoor voices 
from both of you!
